# Backend Rules

## FastAPI patterns
- Every endpoint must be async
- Routers validate input, call a service, return output, nothing more
- Services never import from routers
- Use FastAPI Depends for shared resources like Qdrant client and settings
- Every endpoint must have a docstring
- HTTP status codes:
  - 202 for accepted async jobs
  - 404 for missing resources
  - 422 handled automatically by Pydantic
  - 500 only for unexpected server errors with a safe message

## Settings pattern
- core/config.py is the single source of truth
- lru_cache on get_settings() so settings load once per process
- All values come from .env via pydantic-settings
- Never read os.environ directly anywhere outside config.py

## Schemas pattern
- All request and response bodies are Pydantic v2 models in models/schemas.py
- Never define inline schemas inside routers or services
- Use Field() with descriptions for all schema fields

## Ingestion pipeline
- POST /ingest returns immediately with job_id and status queued
- Processing runs entirely in ARQ worker, never in the request lifecycle
- GET /ingest/status/{job_id} exposes job progress for frontend polling
- Ingestion steps in order:
  1. Parse with Unstructured.io
  2. Extract and caption images with GPT-4o vision
  3. Apply hierarchical chunking (512 token small, 2048 token parent)
  4. Embed with text-embedding-3-large
  5. Store in Qdrant and BM25 index
- Every chunk payload must include:
  company_id, document_name, page_number, chunk_type,
  parent_chunk_id, image_path (if applicable)
- Embed this string, not just chunk text:
  "{document_name} | page {page_number} | {section_header} | {chunk_text}"

## Error handling
- Every service function handles its own exceptions
- Raise HTTPException with clear messages from routers
- Log errors with function name, input summary, and exception message
- Failed ARQ jobs must update status to failed with an error message